article.headline: Tulsa 74, SMU 64
article.story: DALLAS -- Ray Reese scored 24 points to lead Tulsa to a 74-64 comeback win over SMU on Saturday night. Ben Uzoh added 20 points for the Golden Hurricane (20-9, 10-4 Conference USA), and Justin Hurtt had 15. Jerome Jordan scored seven points and grabbed 13 rebounds. Paul McCoy scored 16 points to lead SMU (8-19, 2-12). Mouhammad Faye and Bamba Fall scored 12 apiece, and Derek Williams had 10. SMU led 38-29 at halftime before being outscored 45-26 in the second half. Tulsa dominated the boards, outrebounding SMU 44-29. The Golden Hurricane won the game despite shooting 37 percent from the field. SMU shot 44 percent.
